cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper proposes a neural network for inserting object instances into images, which involves determining the location and appearance of the object. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it requires understanding the semantic context of the image and generating new content. The use of generative modules and spatial transformation networks also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves manipulating images and semantic label maps, which could fall under graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
